from hospital transport to the emergency department (ED), to the operating room 
and intensive care unit (ICU).
CONCLUSIONS AND RELEVANCE: The burden of sTBI is highest in RLRs. As working-age 
adults are the predominantly affected age-group, an increase in 
disability-adjusted life years (DALYs) generates a loss of economic growth in 
regions where economic growth is needed most. Four multi-institutional 
collaborations between high-income countries (HICs) and LMICs have developed 
evidence and consensus-based documents focused on capacity building for sTBI 
care as a means of addressing this substantial burden of disease.

